==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waken
<hw>Wak"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
pr.</pos> <conjf>Wakened</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Wakening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>waknen</ets>,
AS. <ets>w⟦ae⟧cnan</ets>; akin to Goth. ga<ets>waknan</ets>. See
<er>Wake</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <def>To wake; to cease to sleep;
to be awakened.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Early, Turnus <qex>wakening</qex> with the light.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waken</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Waken
<hw>Wak"en</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To excite or rouse
from sleep; to wake; to awake; to awaken.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Go,
<xex>waken</xex> Eve.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To excite; to rouse; to move to action; to
awaken.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then Homer's and Tyrtaeus' martial muse⟦br⟧
<qex>Wakened</qex> the world.</q> <rj><qau>Roscommon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Venus now wakes, and <qex>wakens</qex> love.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They introduce⟦br⟧
Their sacred song, and <qex>waken</qex> raptures high.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wakener</ent>⟦br⟧
